                    <comment id="12319693" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 23 Aug 2005 18:51:45 +0100"  >Proposed patch on SharedItemStateManager.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The write lock is downgraded to a read lock before the listeners are notified. That way, the SharedItemStateManager is effectively released for read access, but does not allow modification while the synchronous listeners are notified, giving them a consistent view of the transaction that just completed.</comment>
                    <comment id="12319701" author="dpfister" created="Tue, 23 Aug 2005 20:44:53 +0100"  >Modified LockManagerImpl to not synchronize when updating content since this can clash with the synchronous event listener being called during a store operation.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Fixed in release 239389.</comment>
                    <comment id="12319708" author="dpfister" created="Tue, 23 Aug 2005 23:31:16 +0100"  >Other problem arises.</comment>
                    <comment id="12319711" author="dpfister" created="Wed, 24 Aug 2005 00:10:46 +0100"  >Another concurrency issue: whereas deadlock has now been removed, two competing threads, locking and unlocking at about the same time could invalidate each other&amp;#39;s node representation. Thanks again to Walter Raboch for finding this issue.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Fixed in r239410.</comment>
